title: Galesburg Volleyball: Streaks take Moline, UT
text: Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 10:35 PM Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 10:35 PM QUINCY – The Galesburg High School volleyball team defeated Moline and United Township at the Western Big 6 Quad on Saturday. The Silver Streaks (19-12, 6-4) defeated the Maroons 25-19, 25-17 in their first match. Shayli Florine led Galesburg with seven kills and three blocks. Kaylah Townsell added six kills, two digs and an ace, Yvonne Mixon and Hannah Huppenbaur each had six blocks, Haley Stevenson had five digs and two aces and Kylee Townsell gave out 20 assists for the Streaks. In Match 2, Galesburg needed three sets to get past the Panthers 25-23, 15-25, 25-15. Florine hammered 20 kills and made four blocks. Huppenbaur made six blocks, Stevenson made seven digs and served two aces, Kaylah Townsell made six kills and six digs, Kylee Townsell gave out 30 assists and Brittnee Williams served three aces. Galesburg’s sophomore team also notched a pair of wins over Moline and UT, earning the conference title. The Streaks (22-2, 9-1) opened play with a 22-25, 25-15, 25-22 win over the Maroons. Galesburg’s Serena Bolden was tough at the net with 17 kills and three blocks. Chloe McCarthy had 10 kills, Sam Rogers made 13 digs and gave out 15 assists, Haley Stevenson and Kalisa Pugh each had 10 digs and Megan Lingafelter served two aces for the Streaks. Galesburg downed UT 25-12, 25-22 in Match 2. Bolden had five kills and five blocks, Pugh had three kills, four digs and two aces and Rogers gave out nine assists and had four digs. The Register-Mail
